        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(proxy): apply enhanced NO_PROXY matching to global undici dispatcher (fixes #95998)",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nFixes #95998.\n\nWhen `HTTPS_PROXY` is set, the global EnvHttpProxyAgent routes ALL requests through the proxy — including internal plugin requests that should bypass via `NO_PROXY`. The built-in undici NO_PROXY matcher does not support leading-dot subdomain patterns, CIDR notation, or octet wildcards.\n\nOpenClaw already has `matchesNoProxy()` that handles these — but it was only used by provider helpers, not the global dispatcher.\n\n## Changes Made\n\n1. **NO_PROXY-aware proxy dispatcher** — Wraps every EnvHttpProxyAgent with a Proxy that checks `matchesNoProxy()` before dispatching. Bypassed requests are routed through a direct Agent with the same timeout and connect policy.\n\n2. **Lifecycle synchronization** — `close()` and `destroy()` now await both the proxy dispatcher AND the bypass Agent before firing the completion callback (addresses Codex P1 finding).\n\n3. **Timeout/connect consistency** — `forceResetGlobalDispatcher` now passes `connect` options to the bypass agent, matching `ensureGlobalUndiciEnvProxyDispatcher` and `applyGlobalDispatcherStreamTimeouts` (addresses Codex P2 finding).\n\n## Evidence\n\n**Proof from unit tests (35 tests):**\n```\n$ npx vitest run src/infra/net/undici-global-dispatcher.test.ts\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  35 passed (35)\n```\n\n**Sibling comparison:**\n- #96034 (liuhao1024): same issue, smaller diff (+84), 🧂 unranked krab\n- #97234 (original, now closed): earlier version of same approach, 🦐 gold shrimp\n- This PR incorporates Codex P1/P2 fixes from original #97234 review\n\n## AI Assistance\n- **AI-assisted**: Yes\n- **Co-Authored-By**: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>\n",
